-- Turkish Stocks: Alcatel Teletas, Adana Cimento, Atac, Isbank
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-03-02T16:29:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-02/turkish-stocks-alcatel-teletas-adana-cimento-atac-isbank.html
Turkey ’s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  climbed 0.3 percent to 60,902.41 at the close in Istanbul,
bringing its gain for the week to 2 percent. Trade on the
exchange was halted throughout the morning session due to a
technical malfunction and began at 2:20 p.m.  The following stocks were active. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  Adana Cimento Sanayii TAS (ADANA)  , a cement maker, fell
1.3 percent to 79 kurus after saying it would pay a dividend of
0.04 lira per C-class share. The A-class shares, on which it
will pay a dividend of 0.39 lira per share, rose 2.1 percent to
3.81 liras.  Alcatel Lucent Teletas Telekomunikasyon AS (ALCTL)  , the
Turkish unit of  Alcatel-Lucent (ALU) , added 1.6 percent to 3.23 liras,
its highest since Dec. 20. The company expects to sign a
contract for a 30 million-euro ($40 million) project with  Turk
Telekomunikasyon AS (TTKOM) , it said in a statement to the exchange
today.  Atac Insaat & Sanayi AS (ATAC)  (ATAC TI), a builder, jumped 1.7
percent to 6.12 liras, closing at an all-time high, after saying
its unit Doruk Iletisim & Otomasyon Sanayi &  Ticaret AS (MGROS)  will
start the process for an initial public offering.  Turkiye Is Bankasi (ISATR)  AS, Turkey’s biggest bank by
assets, fell 0.2 percent to 4.16 liras, trailing a 0.6 percent
increase on the overall bank index. The bank was cut to “sell”
from “neutral” at UBS AG.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
